      <section eId="sec_CCRP-800">
        <num>CCRP 800</num>
        <heading>Section </heading>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-800__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>A defendant may not assign as error a ruling refusing to sustain a
challenge for cause made by him, unless an objection thereto is made at the
time of the ruling.  The nature of the objection and grounds therefor shall be
stated at the time of objection.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-800__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The erroneous allowance to the state of a challenge for cause does
not afford the defendant a ground for complaint, unless the effect of such
ruling is the exercise by the state of more peremptory challenges than it is
entitled to by law.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=112798</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
